Selenium Python test script with Firefox Webdriver. [ Firefox has to be installed if not present ]

There are two test scripts which tests two possible control flows(navigation) for this app. These test scripts require
python selenium package to be installed. It can be installed with the below command.

$pip install selenium

Test cases in testcase1.py :
	Checks the navigation of web pages in the app for a new user and verifies for its correctness by inserting appropriate asserts.

Test cases in testcase2.py
    Checks the navigation of web pages in the app for an existing user and verifies for its correctness by inserting appropriate asserts.
    	
Both the test cases would require Gmail authentication and you need to modify the scripts with appropriate gmail id and password.

The scripts can be run as follows.

$python testcase1.py
$python testcase2.py



END